      "lineNbr": 174,
      "author": {
        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-16T15:22:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For SPIR-V, there\u0027s a \"relaxed precision\" annotation you can attach to variables, and it works similarly in that it infers the precision of other things based on context. This is more about spelling it out so it\u0027s explicit; in a near-future CL I\u0027ll be enforcing that these match.",
      "parentUuid": "8b2df126_fc85d24d",
      "revId": "b900eae97ec7a6219d908211e0f4fa90322b58b1",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
